<br>
&quot;My love,<br>
I have finished with the things I was called away do to, and I now am free to return to you.  Meet me at our place under the stars tomorrow eve, let us join together once again in the love that we both share for each other.<br>
<br>
I look forward to being in your embrace again.<br>
<br>
-Fenwyn&quot;<br>
<br>
His violet eyes smoldered as a voice spoke within.  &quot;She be mine!  Ye cannot have her ye vile thing.&quot;<br>
Angrily he whispered out &quot;Begone you, she is not yours.  I am her master.  She will do what I say, and she will obey me.  If only I could kill you...&quot; his voice spoke dripping with hate.<br>
<br>
Again the voice cried out in his head, &quot;Ye cannot, fer without me, ye would not exist.  Ferget that not dark elf.  That woman needin love and tenderness, not yer foul ways. Not yo..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;SILENCE!&quot; Hakkin shouted out, standing up, a feral look upon his face.  He stood there breathing heavy, his eyes closed.<br>
<br>
He felt lips press against his, and the scent of the woman he had married filled his sense of smell, the taste of her lips upon his made his heart jump..then grow cold.<br>
<br>
A lamented sigh was heard in his mind as his eyes opened.  Fenwyn, drew back, sensing something was not quite right.<br>
<br>
&quot;Love..?&quot; she reached out to caress his face.  <br>
<br>
&quot;I am your Master, Fenwyn.  Or have you forgotten that in your time away from me?  Did the dwarf give you too much tenderness and make you weak?&quot;  He sneered, reached out and struck her with the back of his hand, dropping her to her knees.  All Fenwyn could do was look at him in shock as he stared down at her.  It would quickly be replaced by the non-expressive face that she wore for so long after her time as a captive of the Shadow Guard.  Her head bowed, but a single tear rolled down her cheek.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have displeased you my Master..&quot; her monotone voice replied, yet with a hint of sadness.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, you come here looking for affection that is no longer here.  You gave your life to me, it is mine to control Fenwyn.  You came here having forgot that.  I am glad to see that your...conditioning is still in tact at least.  That stupid pitiful dwarf did much to corrupt it.  Your time with that..family of yours had done much to corrupt it as well.  You belong to the Tier'dal...to me!<br>
<br>
&quot;We have a new family now Fenwyn.  I shed the noble dwarf's ideas as well as shed his family for a new one, a new life.  You will follow me there.  It is not a request, do you understand me?&quot;<br>
<br>
The words filled with hatred and venom pounded her ears, her mind.  Her conditioning kept her from outwardly crying, but inside Fenwyn felt as if she had just died.  The one person that loved her more than anything else in this world seemed to have died as well, and in his place a monster, one out of her past, now directing her future.  Yet, the conditioning kept her from doing anything but obey him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, Master.  I understand.&quot; <p><br>
