The dark elf was lean and muscular.  He wore plate armor, dyed dark red, like drying blood.  He carried upon his back a large sword, well oiled, yet showing signs of use.  He had just returned to Neriak from the Oasis, a message beckoned him to.<br>
<br>
He strode into the empty room, removing his helm, laying it on the table at the center of the room, then stood, waiting.<br>
<br>
Valeria strode into the room, wearing a sheer, practically see through robe, some ornate lace undergarments beneath it.  Dark elves were a vain, seductive race, and Valeria was no exception to the rule.  The dark elf male upon seeing her kneeled to one knee, bowing his head low, his forehead touching the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mistress...&quot;he said, but not a hint of respect could be heard within his monotone voice.<br>
<br>
Valeria looked down, her eyes flashing angrily yet amused.  She would have him, no matter how hard he fought.  She was madly in love with him, and his constant spurning of her only pushed her further into the madness of love.  She reached down and grabbed his hair in her hand, pulling him up, kissing him deeply, biting into his lip.  He growled at her as she pulled away, her tongue running seductively over her lips, tasting his blood upon them.  He sneered at her, and touched his now swelling lower lip.<br>
<br>
&quot;Curse you woman...&quot; he started.  Valeria immediately slapped him harshly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Silence!  You know better than to treat me that way!&quot; Valeria snapped back at him.  The dark elf male turned his face back to look at her, spitting blood out on the floor at her feet.  She chose to ignore his latest sign of disrespect, and stepped over to a stand by the bed.  She opened a container, pouring the liquid out into a glass, then turned to him, taking a small sip of it.  His back was to her, and she smiled slightly.  She then placed the glass back on the stand, and picked up another object.  Valeria looked down at it, then back over to the male that would defy her.  <br>
<br>
A sharp crack could be heard beyond the door, and the scream of unexpected pain came in unison to it.  The dark elf male lay on the floor, a blackened burn mark now upon his armor.  Valeria set the object back town, then lightly walked over to the man she desired.  She looked down at him, slowly shaking her head, sighing.  If only he would give himself to her, she would not have to treat him this way, she thought.  A moan escaped from the male, slowly coming back to consiousness.  She walked over and tugged on a rope, then waited.<br>
<br>
Soon, there was a knock at the door.  Valeria opened it, and ordered the servants to strip the male, then drag him over to the wall.  There they stood him up, his head lolling about semi-consious.  His hands were placed in shackles, and then he was let go, hanging limp, the metal of the shackles digging into his skin as his body weight pulled down on his wrists.<br>
<br>
After the servants left, Valeria stood there, looking at him bemused.  She would have him, she thought, yes, he will be hers.<br>
<br>
The dark elf male slowly came back to consiousness.  He groaned as the pain arrested his senses.  His back burned, his wrists were stinging, the muscles straining in them, almost tearing.  His lip was still throbbing, but it was the least of the things that hurt.  He opened his eyes, and his predicament slowly came to a realization in his mind.  His eyes furrowed in anger and hate.<br>
<br>
He lifted his head up to glare at her.  She started to approach him, seductively, desire in her eyes.  <br>
<br>
&quot;You will pay for this...&quot; he hissed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The Present</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Her image changed to his eyes.  Her skin paled, her hair from flowing white mane to a golden one.  Her eyes remained blue, but now went from eyes that belonged to a woman that was in power to the ones that had sadness in them...regret, fear, hate, love...hope.  Her body moved seductively, but not because of a desire to, but because it had been trained to.  <br>
<br>
She approached him, yet he could still see her..still see Valeria approaching him.  It had to be her he thought. An evil grin spread over his face.  Yes, she would pay.  She would pay dearly for all the pain she caused  him, for the eternity of death and life she condemned him to.<br>
<br>
She would pay.  He was now the Master.<br>
